# Product Requirements Document (PRD): Smart Community Health

## 1. Executive Summary
**Smart Community Health** is a comprehensive, AI-driven digital health ecosystem designed for rural and tribal communities, specifically tailored for the North East India context. The platform bridges the gap between villagers ("Localites"), frontline community health workers ("ASHA"), and formal healthcare facilities ("Clinics") to enable proactive disease surveillance, water quality monitoring, and immediate health assistance.

## 2. Design Architecture

The system follows a hub-and-spoke model where the Mobile App (Edge) acts as the primary data collector, syncing to a Central Server (Cloud) which orchestrates AI and Analytics.

### 2.1. System Overview
```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph "Mobile App (Edge)"
        L[Localite UI]
        A[ASHA UI]
        DB[(SQLite Queue)]
    end

    subgraph "Backend Server (Cloud)"
        API[Express API]
        PG[(PostgreSQL)]
        Worker[Alert Engine]
    end

    subgraph "AI Engines"
        Sarvam[Sarvam AI: Voice/Chat]
        Groq[Groq: Analysis/Triage]
    end

    L <--> API
    A <--> API
    API <--> PG
    API <--> Sarvam
    API <--> Groq
    API <--> DB
```

### 2.2. Component Interaction
1.  **Offline-First**: Mobile apps interact with a local **SQLite** queue when internet is unavailable.
2.  **API Gateway**: A **Node.js/Express** server handles authentication, data validation, and AI orchestration.
3.  **Surveillance Engine**: A background worker analyzes incoming reports to detect clusters and trigger alerts.

---

## 3. Database Schema

### 3.1. Central Database (PostgreSQL)
The core source of truth for all health and environmental data.

